  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Level of soluble Ve-cadherin and antibody VE-cadherin with ELISA TEST in Scleroderma group versus Primary Raynaud's Phenomenon</measure>
    <time_frame>At 30 days average</time_frame>
    <description>Level of human sVE and antibody VE-cadherin in blood will be determined by ELISA test in both groups Scleroderma and Primary Raynaud's Phenomenon.
The methodology of dosage of sVE is based on the pattern:WO/2008/062314 The methodolody of the dosage of antibody VE-cadherin is based on the pattern WO/2012/136820 .
Group Scleroderma (N=60) versus Primary Raynaud's Phenomenon (N=20). Shapiro test.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
